I"uH<p>Usually when you are using a graphical modeler, you do most of the actions with the mouse. <a href="http://www.eclipse.org/sirius">Sirius</a> based modelers have several built-in shortcut keys that you can use to save time in your day to day workflow. Shortcut keys are commonly accessed by using the <img src="https://github.com/mbats/sirius-blog/blob/master/keyboard/blog/images/computer_key_Alt_T.png?raw=true" alt="" /> key, <img src="https://github.com/mbats/sirius-blog/blob/master/keyboard/blog/images/computer_key_Ctrl_T.png?raw=true" alt="" /> key, or <img src="https://github.com/mbats/sirius-blog/blob/master/keyboard/blog/images/computer_key_Shift_T.png?raw=true" alt="" /> key in conjunction with other keys.</p>

<ol>
  <li><a href="#Keyboardsshortcuts">Keyboards shortcuts</a>
    <ol>
      <li><a href="#Commonshortcuts">Common shortcuts</a></li>
      <li><a href="#Diagramshortcuts">Diagram shortcuts</a>
